```bash
CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -trimpath -ldflags="-s -w -X main.version=$VERSION" -o bin/ ./cmd/...
```

| Flag | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `CGO_ENABLED=0` | Pure Go static binary; no C dependencies; required for cross-compilation |
| `-trimpath` | Removes local filesystem paths; enables reproducible builds |
| `-s` | Strips symbol table from binary (~20% smaller) |
| `-w` | Strips DWARF debug info from binary (~10% smaller) |
| `-X main.version=$VERSION` | Injects version string at link time; variable must be `var version string` in `main` |
| `-o bin/` | Output directory for compiled binaries |
